24/06/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Justice Minister Meri Mladenovska-Gjergievska will represent Macedonia at a 30 June hearing at the UN war crimes tribunal in The Hague. That is when requests for the provisional releases of Ljube Boskovski and Johan Tarculovski will be reviewed. Skopje has agreed to guarantee that the former senior interior ministry officials will return to The Hague when their trial starts. (Dnevnik, BBC - 24/06/05; MIA, A1 TV - 23/06/05) 
